14. If you have multiple founders, how did you meet?
The founding team met through a mutual interest in blockchain technology and decentralized gaming. They have been collaborating on various projects and have a shared vision for building a robust, decentralized gaming infrastructure.

15. How many projects have you worked on together? How are responsibilities divided among the founders?
The founding team has worked on multiple projects together, including developing decentralized gaming protocols and blockchain-based solutions. Responsibilities are divided as follows:
- Amar Singh Bedi (CEO): Leads the overall strategy, product vision, and ensures the company stays aligned with its mission.
- Jay McCarthy (CBO): Focuses on fundraising, capital markets, and ensuring financial stability and growth.
- Ken Anderson (CTO): Oversees the technical development, ensuring the protocol is robust and secure, and drives the development of the consensus engine.

16. Is the founding team committed full-time to this project? If not, please explain any other commitments and how much time each founder currently spends on the project.
Yes, the founding team is committed full-time to this project. Each founder dedicates their full professional time to Tashi Protocol.

